<subSubSection id="C32DF1FFFFC9AE6B89D2FCB7EA2FF4C2" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B88A274FFC9AE6B89D2FCB7EA2FF4C2" blockId="5.[151,1436,858,1000]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="B9437E66FFC9AE6B89D2FCB7EF6CF45E" bold="true" box="[151,301,858,884]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Etymology:</emphasis>
—Since the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C37D9F7FFC9AE6B8B55FCB7EDFEF45E" authority="Baker (1878: 263)" authorityName="Baker" authorityPageNumber="263" authorityYear="1878" box="[528,959,858,884]" class="Liliopsida" family="Xanthorrhoeaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angolensis">
<emphasis id="B9437E66FFC9AE6B8B55FCB7EC92F459" box="[528,723,858,883]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Aloe angolensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA6DF85FFC9AE6B8B98FCB7EDFEF45E" author="Baker, J. G." box="[733,959,858,884]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" pagination="245 - 273" refId="ref4509" refString="Baker, J. G. (1878) Report on the Liliaceae, Iridaceae, Hypoxidaceae and Haemodoraceae of Welwitsch's Angolan Herbarium. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, 2 nd series, 1: 245 - 273." type="journal article" year="1878">Baker (1878: 263)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
already exists, this combination is not available for 
<taxonomicName id="4C37D9F7FFC9AE6B8878FC6CEC27F4B0" box="[317,614,897,922]" class="Liliopsida" family="Xanthorrhoeaceae" genus="Chortolirion" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angolensis">
<emphasis id="B9437E66FFC9AE6B8878FC6CEC27F4B0" box="[317,614,897,922]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Chortolirion angolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The new name commemorates Friedrich Martin Josef Welwitsch (1806–1872), who collected the 
<typeStatus id="548C1CD6FFC9AE6B8B7DFC45EC2FF4E8" box="[568,622,936,962]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">type</typeStatus>
specimen and is estimated to have made over 10,000 botanical collections in 
<collectingCountry id="F320E2E4FFC9AE6B887EFC23EFD5F4C2" box="[315,404,974,1000]" name="Angola" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Angola</collectingCountry>
, representing around 5,000 species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA6DF85FFC9AE6B8A7BFC23EA23F4C2" author="Albuquerque, S. &amp; Brummitt, R. K. &amp; Figueiredo, E." box="[830,1122,974,1000]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" pagination="641 - 646" refId="ref4385" refString="Albuquerque, S., Brummitt, R. K. &amp; Figueiredo, E. (2009) Typification of names based on the Angolan collections of Friedrich Welwitsch. Taxon 58: 641 - 646." type="journal article" year="2009">
Albuquerque 
<emphasis id="B9437E66FFC9AE6B8AA5FC22EA5AF4C2" box="[992,1051,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
